value: Breeds from central Alaska, northern Mackenzie, Great Slave Lake, southwestern shores of Hudson Bay and western Ontario south through central British Columbia to northern Montana; south also to Alberta and Manitoba. Winters mainly in the United States and on the Pacific coast to the Aleutian and Commander Islands.

value: Lakes and ponds, nesting in tree cavities in mixed coniferous-deciduous and deciduous woodland; in winter, bays, estuaries, lakes, and slow-moving rivers.
